com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.utilities

Class MultiThreadedProcessingSystem<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.utilities.MultiThreadedProcessingSystem<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - 

    public abstract class MultiThreadedProcessingSystem<T>
extends Object
    A utility class providing a system in which a number of elements are each independently processed in some way (in multiple threads) before calling finishedProcessing on each element in the same order as they originally came in.

    Usage:

    1) Call add(Object) for each entry. This is not thread safe.

    2) The MultiThreadedProcessingSystem will invoke process(Object) for each entry, potentially out of order if numberOfProcessingThreads>1 and potentially in a different thread from add(Object)

    3) Then the MultiThreadedProcessingSystem will invoke finishedProcessing(Object) for each entry, guaranteed to be in the same order as they were added but potentially in a different thread from add(Object)

    4) Since the calls to finishedProcessing are guaranteed to be called in order (via synchronization), these results can be passed on to another chained MultiThreadedProcessingSystem via add(Object) without synchronization

    Example: 

        final AtomicLong totalLength = new AtomicLong();
    MultiThreadedProcessingSystem<NucleotideSequenceDocument> processingSystem = new MultiThreadedProcessingSystem<NucleotideSequenceDocument>("testProcess",10,10,Runtime.getRuntime().availableProcessors()) {
    Since:
    API 4.600 (Geneious 6.0.0)
    See Also:
    MultiThreadedTask

    • Constructor Detail

      • MultiThreadedProcessingSystem

        public MultiThreadedProcessingSystem(String threadNamePrefix,
                             int maxBacklogSize,
                             int valuesPerBacklogEntry,
                             int numberOfProcessingThreads)
        Parameters:
        threadNamePrefix - a prefix for the name to use for any threads created
        maxBacklogSize - the maximum number of batches of valuesPerBacklogEntry entries to store in memory ready awaiting processing. add(Object) will block as long as this threshold is reached.
        valuesPerBacklogEntry - the number of entries added using add(Object) to process in a block. Up to this many entries will passed to batchProcess(java.util.List)
        numberOfProcessingThreads - the number of threads to use for processing once a minimum number of items have been added as specified by setThresholdToStartThreads(int). You may want to use Runtime.getRuntime().availableProcessors()

    • Method Detail

      • setThresholdToStartThreads

        public void setThresholdToStartThreads(int thresholdToStartThreads)
        Sets a threshold for the number of items to be added before this processing systems starts creating additional threads. The default value is 1000. This is to prevent thread overhead from impacting performance on small cases where it is unnecessary.
        Parameters:
        thresholdToStartThreads - the number of items to be be added before this processing systems starts creating additional threads

      • add

        public void add(T entry)
         throws DocumentOperationException
        Adds a new entry to be processed. This entry may be processed in this or a background thread. This method may block if there are too many entries awaiting processing as defined in the constructor.
        Parameters:
        entry - the entry to be processed.
        Throws:
        DocumentOperationException - if the processing method (process(Object) throws a DocumentOperationException

      • batchProcess

        protected void batchProcess(List<T> values)
                     throws DocumentOperationException
        Processes multiple values in a single thread. A subclass my optionally override this to allow improved performance. The default implementation just calls process(Object) for each value.
        Parameters:
        values - all the values to process
        Throws:
        DocumentOperationException - if there is a problem processing any of the entries

        Parameters:
        t - the entry to process
        Throws:

      • finishedProcessing

        public void finishedProcessing(T entry)
                        throws DocumentOperationException
        An implementation may optionally override this to perform any additional cleanup. This is guaranteed to be called for each entry in the same order as they were originally added.
        Parameters:
        entry - the entry that has been processed.
        Throws:
        DocumentOperationException - if there is a problem completing processing of the entry

      • waitForCompletion

        public void waitForCompletion()
                       throws DocumentOperationException

        Throws:
        DocumentOperationException - if either process(Object) or finishedProcessing(Object) threw a DocumentOperationException
